Pros:
- Sharp and responsive interface;
- Amazing mechanics and lots options to play.

Cons:
- Abusive anti-cheat and DRM software (I wanna play single player FFS!);
- Weird key sounds (music gets choppy and just sounds bad) that you cannot turn off;
- Meh songs. This is a personal one I guess;
- Interface not compatible with controllers.

Maybe in the future if they update with more options and remove the bs software, I'll give it another shot. For now is back to clone hero.

9 out of 10 doctors' reports said DJMAX RESPECT V is good for both a die-hard fan of rhythm games (Tapsonic, Cytus, Maimai, Vortex overload, cubeat, etc.). And what about another one, you ask? Well, they're too busy treating those who got Carpal tunnel and Trigger fingers.
//For a more serious review: IMO, this game is very entertaining but learning and mastering the control is pretty tough for Mobile/Tablet and arcade player like me. For now the best I can do is passing a level 8, 6 buttons stage with an A. I can still get a feeling that I'm not one with the control.
PS. I don't really care about the xigncode anti-cheat which popping-up in nearly every Korean online game I've been crossing path with. So if you're looking for some good quality, fun yet a lil bit competitive if you want to, DJ MAX is for you. The only thing I wish for now is more songs from both DJMAX and mainstream (or not mainstream as long as it's good it grab my attention and money).
